Don't be fooled by the outside plaza, this place is good. Really good stuff. It has a mom and pop kind of a feel coming inside. Totally family owned.  Fresh and great ingredients. There is a spice factor multiplier here. I usually an handle my spiciness, but after coming here it definitely brought my A-game to a whole new level. If you feel like a "4" on the spicy level.. go with a 3! The food does take awhile to get prepared, so plan out your time accordingly. Pad Thai is great!

